 there own will.  BUT the officers and leaders i think have a little more impact on the rest of SM.  It shows that noone wants the resposibility of leading or even Co-Leading.   Some of the oldest members of SM have left and there isnt anything any of us can do about it. <br>     <br>     As for me thinking of leaving SM i have many times contenplated &lt;sp&gt; joining other guilds.  Grey Soldiers would gladly have me as for an open invite to ADD.  I was offered by a member of VM to apply to join them as well.  Did i take these NO!!   Will I ??   That all depends on the state of SM when i return. If I think that SM is falling appart upon my return then i will either find someone that wants to lead it or i will choose someone weather they like it or not.  What they do with it will be up to them.   Like many have stated SM was a guild made for Friends to play with Friends.  I truely hope one of those origanal friends takes good care of the guild if not it will be as others have said a &quot;dead guild&quot;.<br><br>                                   <br><br>                                           <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub51.ezboard.com/ustrydr69.showPublicProfile?language=EN>strydr69</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>All-weather Mountaineer</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#333333>(2/28/02 5:50:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub51.ezboard.com/fstormmountainfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=84.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Came off Wrong</span><hr size=1> well ..........ill tell ya what doom...i know what you are trying to say...and if you want to run off with someother guilds when you get back..thats fine...ill take sm.....<br>not that i really play enough to take on the responsibility of running a guild...or that i even want to...<br>but i want to keep it...so even if it ends up to just be me and a couple friends...like dyr and tackk that dont play allot or just as a place for me and my mia friends to get together...so should cend...silver ...souls...gluas...tendra..balroth..you..etc..etc..<br>ever all come back to playing and just want a relaxing home for friends we will be here...i hope of course all the cool peeps we have with us now will stay...but if anyone needs a break..or to uber raid etc..for a while ....hell take one...<br>but id like to keep the guild as a home.....as long as i play or have strydr......and sence very very few have even bothered to vote on leadership...and many have left straight out cause of the situation...etc...not to mention many who have been voted on...have turned the spot down...well...<br>ill take it and deal ..if no one who is a super dedicated leader type will... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub51.ezboard.com/utack91.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tack91</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>All-weather Mountaineer</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(2/28/02 7:01:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub51.ezboard.com/fstormmountainfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=84.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Came off Wrong</span><hr size=1> Doom you shouldn't have to apologize for your post. I dont think you said anything wrong. You simply expressed you disappointment. I felt the same way when I read your post not knowing the new leadership quit. Everyones right. Its no ones business why anyone quits the guild to move on. What makes me sick is the big deal people make about it. If a big drama isn't made about it, it wouldn't be such a big deal anyway. I have been in this guild awhile now and have seen many people leave. Some friends and some not. But I could care less that they leave. Maybe I wont see them around as much as before, or maybe I wont see them at all anymore. I'll tell you I never lost any sleep over it. Another thing that gets me is all the people past and present that have left that say they dont do it to get &quot;uber&quot; they just need a break. It makes me laugh the next day they are in a new more &quot;uber&quot; guild. If you need a break from the game take one. If you want to leave the guild cause you want to get more powerful do it. Just dont try to pull the wool over everyones eyes with an excuse why you want to leave. This post is directed towards no one in particular. If it was I would have stated names. Goes to anyone that has left the guild since i have been in it. So take it as you will I was simply stating my feeling. Peace I'm out. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub51.ezboard.com/fstormmountainfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=84.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub51.ezboard.com/fstormmountainfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=84.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub51.ezboard.com/fstormmountainfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=84.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub51.ezboard.com/fstormmountainfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=84.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub51.ezboard.com/fstormmountainfrm1.threadControl?topicID=84.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub51.ezboard.com/fstormmountainfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=84.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of repl